column2: State underway with API projects. Currently in procurement status. Implementation start expected in January 2024 with completion estimated as late as summer 2025.

The State Interoperability System consists of the following three components.
A) An online portal for third-party apps to register their apps.
B) An online portal for members to complete their digital registration with the State, including conducting identity proofing with ID.me
C) The FHIR Engine services the patient and Provider API data through the State API gateway.
The system became operational on 09/30/2022.
 The State continued to correct historical claims data in the FHIR Engine data store past 09/30/2022 for the next couple of months to address the data discrepancies discovered during our internal testing.
column3:
As of now there has not been any usage of the system. There has been no third party application developers requesting access to these APIs.
For response to Question in Column G, please note this explanation. The member are required to issue explicit consent to any and every third party app before their data is shared via the app. The members can revoke consent to any third party app through the screens.
column5: All support request for Interoperability are being captured via the email as noted in column F. There is no dedicated phone number for this initiative.
column10: Formulary File information is provided as a part of the Provider API
column18: Member are required to be Identity Proofed once with the ID.Me. All members who are identity proofed are authenticated against the State's Identity Provider- Azure B2C. The  protocol used is OAUTH2.0 protocol and OIDC. The JWT Tokens are generated by the Identity provider and validated at the API Gateway.
